article.description:
Candice Dupree scored 29 points, including
the game-winning three-point play with 2.8 seconds remaining in
overtime, to lead No. 23 Temple to a 66-64 victory over La Salle on
Sunday.
article.headline: Dupree's 3-point play lifts Temple past La Salle in OT
article.linkText: Dupree's 3-point play lifts Temple past La Salle in OT
article.story:
PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Candice Dupree scored 29 points, including
the game-winning three-point play with 2.8 seconds remaining in
overtime, to lead Temple (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today; No. 24 AP) to a 66-64 victory over La Salle on
Sunday.

It was Temple's 24th consecutive Atlantic 10 Conference victory.

After a three-point play by Crista Ricketts gave the Explorers a
64-63 lead with 4.2 seconds remaining in the extra session, the
Owls (10-3, 2-0) had to go the length of the court.

Lady Comfort passed to Dupree at the opposite foul line, and
Dupree drove to the basket and was fouled by Ricketts for the
decisive basket.

Kamesha Hairston added 13 points and Khadija Bowens had 10 for
Temple.

Davineia Payne led the Explorers (5-8, 2-1) with 21 points,
while Carlene Hightower had 16 and Ricketts added 11.

La Salle nearly won the game in regulation after Ricketts was
fouled by Jennifer Owens with 5.4 seconds left. Ricketts made the
first free throw, but missed the second and the game went into
overtime tied at 55.
